Enhanced transcription batch 13: book-002 pp163-167

All five pages are leaves of Emma Dee Walker Corbell's August 1940
pencil letter from Richmond to her mother (the compiler). Bodies were
already accurate first-pass; this round confirmed wording against
enhanced crops and tightened frontmatter.

- p163: opening page (Saturday — Mother Dearest —), no corrections
- p164: china price list / flood news, added Richmond, Virginia to places
- p165: Hand to state -> Grand to state (capital G, matches "grand help")
- p166: confirmed 'feel','Think','tomorrow' hyphenation, trailing 'to'
- p167: removed Aunt Anne from people/title/notes — antecedent lives on
  the previous leaf; not actually mentioned on this page

64 of 72 letters complete.
